Accuracy: “How often am I correct overall?”
→ Out of all predictions, how many did you get right.
Precision: “When I say ‘yes’, how often am I right?”
→ Focuses on the quality of positive predictions (avoids false alarms).
Recall: “Out of all actual ‘yes’ cases, how many did I catch?”
→ Focuses on not missing real positives.
F1 Score: “Balance between precision and recall”
→ A single score that combines both (useful when you want a trade-off).
